cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.HC 

This paper is primarily focused on comparing the performance of humans and deep neural networks on object recognition under different types of image degradations. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper discusses the generalization abilities of deep neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the challenges faced by deep learning vision systems, which could place it in the sub-categories cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
